Here are CCEE-oriented MCQs for PG-DITISS ‚Äì Programming Concepts (MySQL) on the topic:

MySQL: Concepts of Databases, Tables, and Schemas
üîπ BASIC LEVEL (10 MCQs)
1. In MySQL, a database is best described as:
A. A collection of rows
B. A collection of columns
C. A collection of related tables
D. A collection of indexes

2. Which SQL command is used to create a database in MySQL?
A. MAKE DATABASE
B. CREATE DB
C. CREATE DATABASE
D. NEW DATABASE

3. Which statement selects a database for use?
A. USE database_name
B. SELECT database_name
C. OPEN database_name
D. SET database_name

4. A table in MySQL consists of:
A. Only rows
B. Only columns
C. Rows and columns
D. Files and indexes

5. What uniquely identifies each row in a table?
A. Column
B. Primary Key
C. Schema
D. Index

6. Which data structure is used to store data in MySQL?
A. File
B. Object
C. Table
D. Schema

7. A schema in MySQL is:
A. Same as a table
B. Same as a database
C. A backup file
D. A view

8. Which command lists all databases in MySQL?
A. SHOW TABLES;
B. SHOW SCHEMAS;
C. SHOW DATABASES;
D. LIST DATABASES;

9. What is the default schema when a database is created?
A. public
B. mysql
C. Same name as database
D. information_schema

10. Which command removes a database permanently?
A. DELETE DATABASE
B. DROP DATABASE
C. REMOVE DATABASE
D. ERASE DATABASE

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL (10 MCQs)
11. Which statement is TRUE about schemas in MySQL?
A. One database can have multiple schemas
B. Schema and database are synonyms
C. Schema stores only metadata
D. Schema exists outside database

12. What happens if you create a table without selecting a database?
A. Table is created in mysql database
B. Error occurs
C. Table is created in default schema
D. Table is created temporarily

13. Which MySQL schema stores system metadata?
A. sys
B. information_schema
C. mysql
D. performance_schema

14. Which of the following is NOT a valid table constraint?
A. PRIMARY KEY
B. FOREIGN KEY
C. UNIQUE
D. TRIGGER

15. What does SHOW TABLES; display?
A. Tables from all databases
B. Tables from selected database
C. Tables from mysql schema only
D. Temporary tables only

16. Which key enforces entity integrity?
A. Foreign Key
B. Candidate Key
C. Primary Key
D. Composite Key

17. If a database is dropped, what happens to its tables?
A. Tables remain intact
B. Tables are archived
C. Tables are deleted
D. Tables move to mysql schema

18. Which statement about schemas improves security?
A. Schemas allow role-based access
B. Schemas encrypt data
C. Schemas compress tables
D. Schemas replicate data

19. How many primary keys can a table have?
A. Zero
B. One
C. Two
D. Unlimited

20. What is the scope of a table name in MySQL?
A. Global
B. Server-level
C. Database-level
D. Schema-level

üî∫ ADVANCED LEVEL (15 MCQs)
21. Which fully qualified name correctly identifies a table?
A. table_name
B. database.table
C. schema.database.table
D. server.database.table

22. Why does MySQL treat schema and database as identical?
A. SQL standard limitation
B. Storage engine design
C. MySQL architecture choice
D. Backward compatibility

23. Which schema cannot be dropped in MySQL?
A. user_schema
B. sys
C. information_schema
D. test

24. What is stored in information_schema.TABLES?
A. Actual table data
B. Table metadata
C. Table indexes
D. Table triggers

25. Which command shows tables from a specific database without using USE?
A. SHOW TABLES FROM db_name;
B. SHOW db_name.TABLES;
C. LIST TABLES FROM db_name;
D. DISPLAY TABLES db_name;

26. Which operation violates referential integrity?
A. Inserting duplicate primary key
B. Inserting NULL in NOT NULL column
C. Deleting parent row without cascade
D. Creating index

27. In MySQL, schemas help mainly in:
A. Data normalization
B. Logical organization
C. Physical storage
D. Query optimization

28. What happens if two tables in different databases have same name?
A. Conflict occurs
B. Error is thrown
C. Allowed without ambiguity
D. One overrides the other

29. Which schema is performance-focused?
A. mysql
B. sys
C. information_schema
D. performance_schema

30. What is the main role of the mysql schema?
A. User data storage
B. Query optimization
C. Privilege management
D. Table metadata

31. Which command renames a database in MySQL?
A. RENAME DATABASE
B. ALTER DATABASE
C. Not directly supported
D. MOVE DATABASE

32. Which object logically belongs inside a schema?
A. Database server
B. Tables
C. Disk files
D. Network sockets

33. Which constraint ensures domain integrity?
A. PRIMARY KEY
B. FOREIGN KEY
C. CHECK
D. INDEX

34. In CCEE, which scenario best uses schemas?
A. Increasing storage size
B. Separating application modules
C. Speeding up joins
D. Reducing disk I/O

35. Dropping a schema in MySQL effectively means:
A. Dropping tables only
B. Dropping indexes only
C. Dropping database
D. Dropping users

